SIMPLE: peruvian
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peruvian
<hw>Pe*ru"vi*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧ruvien</ets>, Sp. <ets>peruviano</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to Peru, in South America.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos>
<def>A native or an inhabitant of Peru.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Peruvian balsam</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Balsam of
Peru</cref>, under <er>Balsam</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Peruvian
bark</b></col>, <cd>the bitter bark of trees of various species of
Cinchona. It acts as a powerful tonic, and is a remedy for malarial
diseases. This property is due to several alkaloids, as quinine,
cinchonine, etc., and their compounds; -- called also <altname>Jesuit's
bark</altname>, and <altname>cinchona</altname>. See
<er>Cinchona</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pervade</ent>⟦br⟧
